This paper is about advances in sequence-to-sequence modeling for machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various neural network architectures and training techniques, which are relevant to machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional and transformer models, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) tasks, making cs.CV a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses hybrid architectures, which could fall under the category of neural engineering (NE), making it a less likely but still possible sub-category.
